text:
I spent the last weeks trying multiple options to keep track of my home plants. There are countless plant manager apps for mobile devices such as Planta[1], PictureThis or Blossom. They all have something in common: a basically useless free trial, a costly premium version and all of them are sending and storing data somewhere™.<p>After searching for quite a while, I have not found a single self hosted application that I can use to manage my home plants and set up reminders to water&#x2F;fertilize them when they are due. There are dozens of options for farming, crop management or garden automation, but that&#x27;s not what I am looking for.
The only app I found is Happy Plants[2], but it seems abandoned and looks more like an MVP than a stable application.<p>Does somebody have an idea if such a software even exists?<p>[1]: https:&#x2F;&#x2F;getplanta.com&#x2F;
[2]: https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;morkro&#x2F;happy-plants
